The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as segmentation and object recognition, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques and neural networks to solve these tasks suggests that the paper could also be classified under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed spatial ranking module and the use of context information to merge results could also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with natural language processing tasks such as semantic segmentation, which could be classified under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the use of the COCO Panoptic benchmark suggests that the paper could also be classified under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
